  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REAP 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The REAP programme was implemented by a consortia of non-governmental organizations composed of Health Poverty Action (HPA), the Adventist Development and Relief Agency International (ADRA), Link Community Development (LCD), and inHive. The overall objective of the REAP programme was to improve the life chances of the marginalised girls targeted in 28 poor and rural schools in Nyaruguru, Rwanda. InHive supported the programme to develop alumni networks to help address barriers to girls&apos; educational attainment and transition. We provided design, training and ongoing evaluation and support since September 2017, and saw how alumni engagement helped to decline absenteeism, improved careers advice and boosted school&#x2019;s financial resources.</narrative>
  </description>
